title: On My Mind - Inflation: The Devil We Knew
text: Central bankers insist that they don't fear inflation; it's the devil they know. They've defeated it before and are confident that they can bring it under control with minimal economic cost once they decide the time is right. The last time the Fed slayed the inflation dragon, it did so by sending the Fed funds rate soaring to 20% and caused the 1982 recession, which remained the deepest on record until 2009.
